    "text": "Tomorrow — put it tomorrow, and treat it as fixed. The floating rest day isn't working, and today's numbers show the cost of skipping it: your recovery score is 57%, well below your 7-day average recovery of 68%, and you slept 386 minutes, about 16 minutes under your 7-day average of 402 minutes — a weekly average that is itself on the thin side. Your monotony flag sits at 2.2, in the watch zone, which often lines up with exactly this pattern: steady moderate days, no true off day. The restructure: anchor the rest day to a fixed weekday — the day after your hardest session — instead of \"whenever fits\". Volume stays the same; placement does the work. If tomorrow's rest lands, your morning numbers later this week will tell you it counted.",
